  "prompt": "What 6/9 mean in eyesight?",
  "response": "In the context of eyesight, \"6/9\" refers to a measure of visual acuity, specifically using the Snellen chart. The first number (6) represents the distance in meters at which you are standing from the chart. The second number (9) indicates the distance at which a person with normal vision can read the same line of letters.\n\nSo, if your visual acuity is 6/9, it means that you can read at 6 meters what a person with normal vision can read at 9 meters. This is considered slightly below normal vision, as normal vision is typically defined as 6/6. However, 6/9 vision is still quite good and may not require corrective lenses unless it affects your daily activities.",
